1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,348
The four-mode map is not a taxonomy to memorize.

2
00:00:03,298 --> 00:00:05,019
It is a routing tool.

3
00:00:05,019 --> 00:00:13,625
Before the next prompt, identify the uncertainty, the judgment you must keep, the execution the agent can take, and the evidence that will prove the result.

4
00:00:13,625 --> 00:00:17,375
First, Separate human intensity from agent intensity.

5
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:21,625
Second, Match the mode to uncertainty, judgment, and risk.

6
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:25,070
Third, Switch deliberately and keep outcome ownership.

7
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:34,548
Use asking for one bounded uncertainty, collaboration for iterative judgment, exploration for an unstable destination, and delegation for specified execution.

8
00:00:34,548 --> 00:00:37,846
If the task changes, the mode should change with it.

9
00:00:37,846 --> 00:00:47,615
Following practical AI and agent work methods matters because the models will keep changing, while the need to define intent, boundaries, evidence, and responsibility will remain.

10
00:00:47,615 --> 00:00:51,586
Those skills let you use stronger systems without giving up judgment.

11
00:00:51,586 --> 00:00:58,471
On your next task, draw the two axes, choose the smallest useful mode, and write the stop condition before you begin.

12
00:00:58,471 --> 00:01:03,500
That is how an AI workflow becomes more capable and more trustworthy at the same time.
